{
  "texts": [
    "They summarized six narrative visualization genres and categorized them by intelligence and automation levels.",
    "This work is the most relevant to our survey, however, the authors only focused on tools instead of foundation models and detailed techniques.Compared to the above survey papers, we would like to explore how foundation models are used for generating narrative visualizations from different aspects, including analysis, narration, visualization, and interaction.",
    "Especially, a foundation model is any model trained on broad data, typically using self-supervision at scale, which can be adapted (e.g., fine-tuned) to a wide range of downstream tasks.",
    "Current examples include BERT, GPT, and CLIP [4], [48].",
    "In this paper, we focus on models with over 100 million parameters."
  ]
}